# Automating the AWS Resources Tracker script using Cronjob

# Edit the crontab file with root access

Sudo crontab -e

# Now select the text editor you want to choose (example : Vim, Nano etc.,)

# Add the cronjob entry - the script should run daily at 7:30 PM
# modify the below path of your script according to your saved path

30 19 * * * /home/ubuntu/users/AWS_Resources_Tracker.sh

# Save and exit your text editor
# Also make sure your script has the appropriate executable permissions






